results.title: Case report of a phencyclidine false positive due to lamotrigine use with confirmatory testing.
results.text_hl: He had a history of @DISEASE_Bipolar_Disorder @DISEASE_MESH:D001714 @@@Bipolar I@@@, @DISEASE_Stress_Disorders_Post_Traumatic @DISEASE_MESH:D013313 @@@PTSD@@@, @DISEASE_Psychotic_Disorders @DISEASE_MESH:D011618 @@@schizoaffective disorder@@@, @DISEASE_Hypertension @DISEASE_MESH:D006973 @@@hypertension@@@, and @DISEASE_Marijuana_Abuse @DISEASE_MESH:D002189 @@@cannabis@@@/@<m>DISEASE_Opioid_Related_Disorders</m> @DISEASE_MESH:D009293 @@@opioid abuse@@@. His home medications included @CHEMICAL_Paliperidone_Palmitate @CHEMICAL_MESH:D000068882 @@@paliperidone@@@, @CHEMICAL_Duloxetine_Hydrochloride @CHEMICAL_MESH:D000068736 @@@duloxetine@@@, @CHEMICAL_Lamotrigine @CHEMICAL_MESH:D000077213 @@@lamotrigine@@@, @CHEMICAL_tizanidine @CHEMICAL_MESH:C023754 @@@tizanidine@@@, @CHEMICAL_Hydroxyzine @CHEMICAL_MESH:D006919 @@@hydroxyzine@@@, and @<m>CHEMICAL_Lisinopril</m> @CHEMICAL_MESH:D017706 @@@lisinopril@@@.
